modules.description: Provides functions to execute test suites with customizable command-line arguments and configuration options, including timeout settings and output formatting. Works with test cases defined as functions that take an argument and return an asynchronous result, and test suites structured as lists of test cases. Used to run tests with specific CLI configurations, such as enabling verbose output or filtering test execution based on names.

Provides functions to define and execute unit tests, including a check function for asserting conditions and a run function for executing test callbacks. Works with testable values, predicates, and test callbacks to validate code behavior. Used to run targeted tests with colored output, focusing on failures and enabling selective test execution via a query language.

Executes test suites with customizable CLI options, including timeouts and output formats, using asynchronous test cases structured as lists. Accepts functions that take an argument and return a deferred, enabling controlled test execution. Supports filtering tests by name and adjusting behavior through configuration. Examples include running tests with verbose logging or limiting execution to a subset of test cases.
